.TH "LIGHTNING-NODE-VERSION" 1 "May 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-node-version \- report installed software versions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning node-version
.SH DESCRIPTION
Prints a JSON object with installed software versions:
.nf
{"lightning":"1.3.1","cln":"v24.05","bitcoin_network":"bitcoin"}
.fi
.TP
.B lightning
Version of this
.B lightning
frontend package.
.TP
.B cln
Core Lightning daemon version from
.BR lightning-cli (1)
.BR getinfo ,
or
.B null
when the daemon is not reachable.
.TP
.B bitcoin_network
The configured network (bitcoin, testnet, regtest, etc.).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Always.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-node-info (1),
.BR lightning-node-health (1)
